@page "/help/validation-errors"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.Authorize(Policy = "InstitutionUser")]
@inject IJSRuntime JS

<PageTitle>Validation Error Guide — Help Center — RegOS™ Portal</PageTitle>

<HelpLayout>
    <div class="help-article">
        <!-- Article meta -->
        <div class="fc-ha-meta">
            <span class="fc-ha-meta-item">
                <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg>
                8 min read
            </span>
            <span class="fc-ha-meta-item">
                <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="16" y1="2" x2="16" y2="6"/><line x1="8" y1="2" x2="8" y2="6"/><line x1="3" y1="10" x2="21" y2="10"/></svg>
                Updated March 2026
            </span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="help-article-title">Validation Error Guide</h2>
        <p class="help-article-intro">
            When you submit a return, it goes through multiple validation stages. This guide explains
            each error type, what causes it, and how to fix it.
        </p>

        <div class="help-toc">
            <h3 class="help-toc-title">Validation Categories</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#schema">Schema Validation</a></li>
                <li><a href="#typerange">Type &amp; Range Checks</a></li>
                <li><a href="#intrasheet">Intra-Sheet Formula Validation</a></li>
                <li><a href="#crosssheet">Cross-Sheet Validation</a></li>
                <li><a href="#business">Business Rule Validation</a></li>
                <li><a href="#severity">Error vs Warning</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Severity explanation -->
        <section id="severity">
            <h3 class="help-section-heading">Error vs Warning</h3>
            <div class="help-severity-grid">
                <div class="help-severity-card help-severity-error">
                    <h4>
                        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/>
                        </svg>
                        Error
                    </h4>
                    <p>Errors <strong>prevent acceptance</strong> of the submission. You must fix all errors before the return can be accepted. The submission will have a <strong>Rejected</strong> status.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="help-severity-card help-severity-warning">
                    <h4>
                        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                            <path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"/>
                            <line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/>
                        </svg>
                        Warning
                    </h4>
                    <p>Warnings <strong>do not prevent acceptance</strong> but indicate potential data issues that should be reviewed. The submission will have an <strong>Accepted with Warnings</strong> status.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Schema Validation -->
        <section id="schema">
            <h3 class="help-section-heading">
                <span class="help-validation-badge help-badge-schema">Stage 1</span>
                Schema Validation
            </h3>
            <p>Schema validation checks that your XML file is well-formed and conforms to the template's XSD schema. These are always errors (never warnings).</p>

            <div class="help-error-catalog">
                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Invalid XML Structure</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> The XML file is not well-formed — missing closing tags, invalid characters, or malformed elements.</p>
                    <p><strong>Common causes:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Missing closing tags (e.g., <code>&lt;CashInHand&gt;</code> without <code>&lt;/CashInHand&gt;</code>)</li>
                        <li>Special characters not properly escaped (<code>&amp;</code> should be <code>&amp;amp;</code>)</li>
                        <li>File encoding issues — ensure UTF-8 encoding</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Validate your XML with any XML validator tool before submission. Most XML editors highlight structural issues.</p>
                    <button class="fc-hx-trigger" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-schema-1")' type="button">
                        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/><polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/></svg>
                        See what this error looks like in context
                    </button>
                    <div id="ex-schema-1" class="fc-hx-example @(_openExamples.Contains("ex-schema-1") ? "fc-hx--visible" : "")" aria-hidden="@(!_openExamples.Contains("ex-schema-1"))">
                        <div class="fc-hx-header">
                            <span class="fc-hx-badge fc-hx-badge--error">Error: Invalid XML Structure</span>
                            <button class="fc-hx-close" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-schema-1")' type="button" aria-label="Close example">×</button>
                        </div>
                        <div class="fc-hx-mock-form">
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">File</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-error-cell" title="Error highlighted">MFCR300_2024_01.xml <span class="fc-hx-err-indicator">!</span></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Stage</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val">Schema Validation</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Error</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-error-cell">Line 12: Element 'CashInHand' is not closed. Expected '&lt;/CashInHand&gt;'</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-code">
                                <div class="fc-hx-code-ok">  &lt;CashInHand&gt;1500000.00&lt;/CashInHand&gt;</div>
                                <div class="fc-hx-code-bad">  &lt;BalWithCBN&gt;3200000.00  <span class="fc-hx-code-arrow">← missing closing tag</span></div>
                                <div class="fc-hx-code-ok">  &lt;TotalAssets&gt;4700000.00&lt;/TotalAssets&gt;</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Namespace Mismatch</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> The <code>xmlns</code> attribute on the root element doesn't match the expected namespace for the selected template.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Ensure the namespace matches the pattern <code>urn:cbn:dfis:fc:{ReturnCode}</code>. Download the XSD from the <a href="/schemas">Schemas</a> page for reference.</p>
                    <button class="fc-hx-trigger" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-schema-2")' type="button">
                        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/><polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/></svg>
                        See what this error looks like in context
                    </button>
                    <div id="ex-schema-2" class="fc-hx-example @(_openExamples.Contains("ex-schema-2") ? "fc-hx--visible" : "")" aria-hidden="@(!_openExamples.Contains("ex-schema-2"))">
                        <div class="fc-hx-header">
                            <span class="fc-hx-badge fc-hx-badge--error">Error: Namespace Mismatch</span>
                            <button class="fc-hx-close" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-schema-2")' type="button" aria-label="Close example">×</button>
                        </div>
                        <div class="fc-hx-mock-form">
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Template</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val">MFCR 300 — Statement of Assets</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Expected NS</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-code-ref">urn:cbn:dfis:fc:MFCR300</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Found NS</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-error-cell fc-hx-code-ref">urn:cbn:dfis:fc:MFCR310</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="fc-hx-hint">You uploaded a MFCR310 file but selected the MFCR300 template. Fix: update the <code>xmlns</code> attribute in your XML to match the correct return code.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Unknown Element</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> The XML contains elements not defined in the template schema.</p>
                    <p><strong>Common causes:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Typos in element names (XML is case-sensitive)</li>
                        <li>Using elements from a different template version</li>
                        <li>Extra elements not part of the template definition</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Check the <a href="/templates">Template Browser</a> for the correct field names.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Missing Required Element</h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A field marked as required in the template is missing from your XML.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Add the missing element. Use <code>0</code> for numeric fields with no applicable value.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Type & Range -->
        <section id="typerange">
            <h3 class="help-section-heading">
                <span class="help-validation-badge help-badge-typerange">Stage 2</span>
                Type &amp; Range Checks
            </h3>
            <p>These checks verify that each value is the correct data type and falls within acceptable ranges.</p>

            <div class="help-error-catalog">
                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Invalid Data Type <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-1040</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A value doesn't match the expected type (e.g., text in a numeric field).</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> <code>&lt;LoanAmount&gt;five million&lt;/LoanAmount&gt;</code> — expected a number.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Ensure values match the field's data type (Decimal, Integer, Text, Date).</p>
                    <button class="fc-hx-trigger" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-type-1")' type="button">
                        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/><polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/></svg>
                        See error E-1040 in context
                    </button>
                    <div id="ex-type-1" class="fc-hx-example @(_openExamples.Contains("ex-type-1") ? "fc-hx--visible" : "")" aria-hidden="@(!_openExamples.Contains("ex-type-1"))">
                        <div class="fc-hx-header">
                            <span class="fc-hx-badge fc-hx-badge--error">Error E-1040: Invalid Data Type</span>
                            <button class="fc-hx-close" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-type-1")' type="button" aria-label="Close example">×</button>
                        </div>
                        <div class="fc-hx-mock-form">
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Field</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val">LoanAmount (Decimal)</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Your value</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-error-cell">five million <span class="fc-hx-err-indicator">!</span></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Expected</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-ok-cell">5000000.00</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="fc-hx-hint">Numeric fields must contain only digits and a decimal point. No text, commas, or currency symbols.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Value Out of Range <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-1045</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A value exceeds the defined minimum or maximum for the field.</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> An interest rate of <code>150.0</code> when the maximum is <code>100.0</code>.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Check the field definition in the <a href="/templates">Template Browser</a> for min/max constraints.</p>
                    <button class="fc-hx-trigger" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-type-2")' type="button">
                        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/><polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/></svg>
                        See error E-1045 in context
                    </button>
                    <div id="ex-type-2" class="fc-hx-example @(_openExamples.Contains("ex-type-2") ? "fc-hx--visible" : "")" aria-hidden="@(!_openExamples.Contains("ex-type-2"))">
                        <div class="fc-hx-header">
                            <span class="fc-hx-badge fc-hx-badge--error">Error E-1045: Value Out of Range</span>
                            <button class="fc-hx-close" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-type-2")' type="button" aria-label="Close example">×</button>
                        </div>
                        <div class="fc-hx-mock-form">
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Field</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val">InterestRate (0 – 100)</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Your value</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-error-cell">150.00 <span class="fc-hx-err-indicator">!</span></span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row">
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Valid range</span>
                                <span class="fc-hx-mock-val">0.00 – 100.00</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="fc-hx-hint">Interest rates are stored as percentages (e.g., 15.5 for 15.5%), not as decimals (0.155). Check your value interpretation.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Invalid Item Code <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-1050</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> For ItemCoded templates, the <code>&lt;ItemCode&gt;</code> value is not in the predefined catalog.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Use only item codes defined for this template. Browse available codes in the <a href="/templates">Template Browser</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Intra-Sheet -->
        <section id="intrasheet">
            <h3 class="help-section-heading">
                <span class="help-validation-badge help-badge-intrasheet">Stage 3</span>
                Intra-Sheet Formula Validation
            </h3>
            <p>These rules validate arithmetic and logical relationships between fields within the same return. Formulas are defined by the template designer.</p>

            <div class="help-error-catalog">
                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Sum Mismatch <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-2010</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A total field doesn't equal the sum of its component fields.</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> <code>TotalAssets</code> should equal <code>CashInHand + BalWithCBN + ...</code> but the values don't add up.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Recalculate the total field. Some formulas allow a small tolerance.</p>
                    <button class="fc-hx-trigger" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-formula-1")' type="button">
                        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"/><polyline points="8 6 2 12 8 18"/></svg>
                        See error E-2010 in context
                    </button>
                    <div id="ex-formula-1" class="fc-hx-example @(_openExamples.Contains("ex-formula-1") ? "fc-hx--visible" : "")" aria-hidden="@(!_openExamples.Contains("ex-formula-1"))">
                        <div class="fc-hx-header">
                            <span class="fc-hx-badge fc-hx-badge--error">Error E-2010: Sum Mismatch</span>
                            <button class="fc-hx-close" @onclick='() => ToggleExample("ex-formula-1")' type="button" aria-label="Close example">×</button>
                        </div>
                        <div class="fc-hx-mock-form">
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row"><span class="fc-hx-mock-label">CashInHand</span><span class="fc-hx-mock-val">1,500,000.00</span></div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row"><span class="fc-hx-mock-label">BalWithCBN</span><span class="fc-hx-mock-val">3,200,000.00</span></div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row"><span class="fc-hx-mock-label">OtherAssets</span><span class="fc-hx-mock-val">800,000.00</span></div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-sep"></div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row"><span class="fc-hx-mock-label">TotalAssets (reported)</span><span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-error-cell">5,000,000.00 <span class="fc-hx-err-indicator">!</span></span></div>
                            <div class="fc-hx-mock-row"><span class="fc-hx-mock-label">Formula result</span><span class="fc-hx-mock-val fc-hx-ok-cell">5,500,000.00</span></div>
                            <p class="fc-hx-hint">Difference of 500,000 exceeds tolerance. Check that all component fields are included and correctly valued.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Equals / Difference Check Failed <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-2020</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> Two fields that should be equal don't satisfy the condition.</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> <code>TotalAssets</code> must equal <code>TotalLiabilities</code> (balance sheet must balance).</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Review both sides of the equation and correct the discrepancy.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Ratio Check Failed <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-2030</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A computed ratio doesn't match the reported ratio value.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Verify the calculation. The system checks that the ratio field equals the formula result within tolerance.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Threshold Breach <code class="fc-hx-err-code">W-2040</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A value exceeds a regulatory threshold defined by the formula.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Verify the data is correct. If it genuinely exceeds the threshold, the issue may be flagged as a warning rather than an error.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Cross-Sheet -->
        <section id="crosssheet">
            <h3 class="help-section-heading">
                <span class="help-validation-badge help-badge-crosssheet">Stage 4</span>
                Cross-Sheet Validation
            </h3>
            <p>Cross-sheet rules validate consistency between different return templates. A value reported in one return must match a corresponding value in another return.</p>

            <div class="help-error-catalog">
                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Cross-Template Mismatch <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-3010</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A value in this return doesn't match the corresponding value in a related return that was previously submitted.</p>
                    <p><strong>Example:</strong> Total deposits in MFCR 300 should match the sum of deposits in MFCR 310.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Review both returns and ensure consistent values. You may need to correct and re-submit one or both returns.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Missing Related Submission <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-3020</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A cross-sheet rule references another template that hasn't been submitted for the same period.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Submit the related return for the same reporting period first, then re-submit this return.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Business Rules -->
        <section id="business">
            <h3 class="help-section-heading">
                <span class="help-validation-badge help-badge-business">Stage 5</span>
                Business Rule Validation
            </h3>
            <p>Business rules enforce regulatory requirements and data quality standards defined by CBN.</p>

            <div class="help-error-catalog">
                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Completeness Check Failed <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-4010</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> Required sections of the return are incomplete.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Ensure all required fields have non-zero, non-empty values as applicable.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Date Check Failed <code class="fc-hx-err-code">E-4020</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> Date values fall outside the expected range for the reporting period.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Ensure dates are within the reporting period and in <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> format.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="help-error-entry">
                    <h4>Regulatory Threshold Exceeded <code class="fc-hx-err-code">W-4030</code></h4>
                    <p><strong>What it means:</strong> A reported metric exceeds CBN regulatory limits.</p>
                    <p><strong>How to fix:</strong> Verify the data. If correct, the issue may require regulatory disclosure or explanation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <div class="help-next-links">
            <h3>Related Topics</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="/help/submission-guide">Submission Guide</a></li>
                <li><a href="/help/faq">Frequently Asked Questions</a></li>
                <li><a href="/help/support">Contact Support</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <HelpRating ArticleId="validation-errors" />
    </div>
</HelpLayout>

@code {
    private HashSet<string> _openExamples = new();

    private void ToggleExample(string exId)
    {
        if (!_openExamples.Remove(exId))
            _openExamples.Add(exId);
    }
}
